Pippa Middleton gave birth to her son, of eight-pound nine-ounce, at precisely 1:58 p.m on the 15th of October. Kate Middleton and Prince William announced the baby arrival through a Kensington Palace spokesperson. The baby boy, whose name has not yet be revealed, already as a palace of his own to call home. Pippa and James’ five-story townhouse in London was recently renovated to include a new bathroom and his-and-hers dressing rooms along with the in-home gym and underground movie theatre. Image credit: Hola! This baby boy is the first child of Pipa Middleton, Catherine Middleton’s sister, and James Matthews who was a former professional racing driver. 